result.formatted_address: 2F & 3F LKF 29 Building, 29 Wyndham Street, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Picada

reviews.text:
Lovely place to eat some Hispanic food. Their menu is classified into regional taste (jungle, mountain,...)

Good itself is great, tried the charcoal steak, their home made on spot guacamole that you can adjust to your taste and the fried rice with vegetables.

Mind you, pricewise we are a step above a lot of the local restaurant.
But it's well worth the price for me.

Also, on Tuesday it's tacos day, pretty much all you can eat.

The only Latin American fusion place in HK! The main restaurant has excellent fusion dishes along with amazing cocktails and live music with a dance floor. if that's not enough then there's an equally large rooftop above with original signature cocktails and guest DJs. What's not to love?

Attending the Taco Tuesday right now and despite the tacos being delicious, the service is very slow. This wouldn't be a problem if they didn't put a 2 hour limit on the all you can eat tacos (and all you can drink). The slow service could be fixed if they hired more people to work. Either get rid of the 2 hour limit or hire more staff. That is all.
Good vibe and mice environment. Great food and service too. Will definitely come back!

Hey guys, the elevator situation you got there is a little confusing. If we would have arrived at the right entrance, the welcome would have been proper I guess, but we ended up at the rear part of the venue and we stood there as no one knows what to do with us.

Venue itself and hosting was good. Also the event was nice.
